</emphasis>
TL = 9.5, HL =1.3, HW = 1.7, PL = 2.2, PW = 2.4, EL = 6.0, EW = 4.3
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1765,2009]" box="[199,523,1909,1934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1909,1934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Description.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[437,523,1909,1934]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1765,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,292,1945,1970]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Colour:</emphasis>
Head, pronotum and elytra black; antennomeres black and palpomeres brownish red, anterior half of 4th maxillary and labial palpomeres black, rest brownish red.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Head</emphasis>
: Small, shiny, slightly convex in the middle, narrower than pronotum, strongly bulging eyes, long and deep frontal furrows reaching about the level of posterior margin of eye. Labrum small, angles weakly rounded, smooth, anterior margin strongly emarginated, 4 long setae present on anterior margin, both ends of anterior margin with bunch of mini brush like setae. Clypeus smooth, with single long setae on either sides, straight margin. Apical labial and maxillary palpomeres moderately expanded apically. Mandibles fairly short, tip not crossing each other. Vertex roughly punctured. 
<collectingRegion box="[465,560,333,356]" country="Myanmar" name="Chin" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Mentum</collectingRegion>
with subrectangular blunt median tooth, submentum bears 6 setae. Genae briefly setose, gula shiny. Antennae elongate, segments black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Pronotum</emphasis>
: Transverse, wider than head, Dorsal and ventral side roughly punctured and covered by greyish yellow coloured setae, straight anterior and posterior margins, narrowly rounded to the anterior corners, broadest at centre, expands behind the middle, posterior corners obtuse. The lateral marginal edge of the pronotum extremely thin, anterior corner strongly bent. Lateral margin rounded at the middle and sinuate behind the middle. Prosternal process conical with narrow base without margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,545,583,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,583,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Scutellum</emphasis>
: triangular, smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,945,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,358,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Metepisterna</emphasis>
considerably longer than broad; strongly punctured.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,275,655,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Elytra</emphasis>
: Long, highly convex, weakly ovoid, covered with greyish yellow coloured setae, Striae with deep punctures, Intervals weakly convex and punctured, equal in width, apex obliquely truncate and weakly emarginated. Elytral suture line has a narrow gap at the apex and not closed. Projected humerus weakly sloping, slightly rounded on the sides. Widest behind the middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,479,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Hind wing:</emphasis>
fully grown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,1383,836,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,836,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Legs</emphasis>
: Tarsi hairy dorsally and ventrally, thick patch of setae covered in ventral side of all tarsal segments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="363" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,871,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Jithmon &amp; Thomas, 2018" authorityName="Jithmon &amp; Thomas" authorityYear="2018" box="[328,658,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Euschizomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="devagiriensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[328,658,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Euschizomerus devagiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[669,760,872,895]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1869" box="[1047,1160,873,896]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Euschizomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneus">
<emphasis box="[1047,1160,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">E. aeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with slender prosternal process weakly pointed towards apex in contrast to the broad and apically rounded prosternal process in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1869" box="[1327,1436,909,932]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Euschizomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneus">
<emphasis box="[1327,1436,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">E. aeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the lateral margin of pronotum rounded medially while broadly expanded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1869" box="[1057,1166,945,968]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Euschizomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneus">
<emphasis box="[1057,1166,945,968]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">E. aeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
